OL,3,CTeen warned 'today's the day' before
OL,4,Cattack in school, court told
OL,6,FIn another post he referred to a
OL,7,Fsecond staff member as an "absolute
OL,8,Ftraitor", saying: "I haven't forgotten
OL,9,Fyou either."
OL,11,FIn a message read in court he said:
OL,12,F"Today is the day. A calling from the
OL,13,FLord Jesus Christ has been cast upon
OL,14,Fme. To do what God Almighty thinks is
OL,15,Fnecessary."
OL,17,FProsecutor Katy Rafter told the court
OL,18,Fabout a Snapchat conversation, in
OL,19,Fwhich the teenager warned another user
OL,20,Fto stay away from the school on the
OL,21,Fday in question.
