OL,3,CTeen warned 'today's the day' before
OL,4,Cattack in school, court told
OL,6,FMs Rafter said he said he was "going
OL,7,Fto do what needed to be done", that
OL,8,Fthe school was "done for" and that he
OL,9,Fwould be "arrested afterwards, in jail
OL,10,For dead."
OL,12,FShe told the jury: "(The other boy)
OL,13,Fthought he was joking. He was not
OL,14,Fjoking. Having armed himself with
OL,15,Fpieces of broken pieces of glass, he
OL,16,Fwalked from his home address to Birley
OL,17,FAcademy."
