OL,3,CTeen warned 'today's the day' before
OL,4,Cattack in school, court told
OL,6,FThe court heard the defendant went to
OL,7,Fthe school's reception on 1 May and
OL,8,Fasked for a staff member who had not
OL,9,Farrived.
OL,11,FA 12-year-old girl and two friends
OL,12,Fthen entered the area. Ms Rafter said:
OL,13,F"Almost immediately, without warning
OL,14,For provocation, he stabbed (the girl),
OL,15,Fintending to smash the broken glass
OL,16,Finto her."
OL,18,FA youth mentor who was in the area
OL,19,Ftried to intervene and was attacked,
OL,20,Fas a receptionist ushered the three
OL,21,Fgirls away.
