OL,3,CTeen warned 'today's the day' before
OL,4,Cattack in school, court told
OL,6,FWhen he was arrested, the boy made
OL,7,Fcomments about "accepting Jesus Christ
OL,8,Fas your Lord and saviour".
OL,10,FThe court heard neither staff member
OL,11,Fmentioned by the teenager in social
OL,12,Fmedia messages could recall any past
OL,13,Fincidents with him.
OL,15,FHe is accused of three counts of
OL,16,Fattempted grievous bodily harm.
OL,18,FHe has previously admitted two counts
OL,19,Fof unlawful wounding and possession of
OL,20,Fa bladed article on school premises.
